  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "\"Fairness\" ensures that AI applications do not contradict the current societal advocacy for educational fairness, such as embedding gender, racial, ethnic, or economic discrimination into AI algorithms.",
    "\"Cost\" includes the technological risks and negative effects that AI developers should bear, as well as the consequences of technical errors.",
    "Developers should not transfer these costs to users or try to evade responsibility through legal loopholes in user agreements.",
    "Users also bear corresponding risks and costs when using AI, which necessitates ethical standards and regulations to reduce these risks (Nasr et al., 2018; Song et al., 2017).",
    "Utilitarianism is a theory widely applied in the field of ethics, whose core tenet is that the correctness of actions depends on whether they produce the greatest happiness or benefit (Mill, 1863)."
  ],
